In 1890, Raub's population was 100.<ref>{{Cite book |last=Cram |first=George Franklin |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CPAwAQAAMAAJ&dq=cram%2527s+1885+atlas&pg=PA330 |title=Cram's Universal Atlas: Geographical, Astronomical and Historical, Containing a Complete Series of Maps of Modern Geography, Illustrated by Numerous Views and Charts; the Whole Supplemented with Valuable Statistics, Diagrams, and a Complete Gazetteer of the United States |date=1890 |publisher=G.F. Cram |page=366 |language=en}}</ref> The community's population was 108 in 1900.<ref>{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=9AzrWecxN1wC |title=Cram's Modern Atlas: The New Unrivaled |date=1902 |publisher=J. R. Gray & Company |page=138 |language=en}}</ref> In 1920, Raub's population was 258.<ref>{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WqRRAQAAMAAJ |title=Premier Atlas of the World: Containing Maps of All Countries of the World, with the Most Recent Boundary Decisions, and Maps of All the States, territories, and Possessions of the United States with Population Figures from the Latest Official Census Reports, Also Data of Interest Concerning International and Domestic Political Questions |date=1925 |publisher=Rand McNally & Company |page=186 |language=en}}</ref>

In 1960, the population of the community was 100.<ref>{{Cite encyclopedia |year=1960 |title=World Book Encyclopedia |publisher=Field Enterprises Corporation |volume=I |page=153 |language=en}}</ref> In 2020, the population of Raub was 53.<ref name="DecennialCensus"/>

